can the little white mushrooms that grow in your yard make your puppy sick she just started having the runs and throwing up she was outside about an hour ago then she got sick she has had her shots any ideas yes they can make a dog sick my pit bull recently ate one she found in the yard they seem to grow up overnight and she got diarrhea and threw up since she wasn't violently ill i gave her pumpkin pie filling after the first three or four episodes of diarrhea and a few bouts of throwing up i also got her some pedialyte for babies and gave it to her she got better real quick but was not up to her full frisky self for a few days so now i watch her carefully and check the grounds before walking her i'd definitely say go to a vet or talk to an e r vet on the phone so you can see what they recommend you do mine is a two yr old dog and yours is a pup and might get sicker Garfield Kodocha Taikyoku shogi Pumpkin 101 Dalmatians: The Series Joke Diarrhea Guinea pig Sin City Blood (computer game) Sick Puppy Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Housebreaking Scooby-Doo Food American Pit Bull Terrier Beethoven (film) Pie Fecal incontinence Shaggy dog story Toilet humour The Brady Bunch Mario Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Foodborne illness Dog RuneScape quests Shark Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Mushroom hunting Dog training The Ashlee Simpson Show Apollo 8 Humphrey Bogart Escape from New York Sandy Koufax Coeliac disease Professional wrestling aerial techniques Pet skunk New York Giants Hamster Gray Wolf Vampire The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron: Boy Genius Sperm Whale Prostate cancer Hip hop rivalries Full Metal Panic? Fumoffu Skinny Puppy Our Gang German Shepherd Dog The Shining (film) Iditarod Ron and Fez Pete the Pup Into the West (miniseries) Pit bull Fancy rat Sea-Monkey USS Tunny (SS-282) Super Mario Bros. 3 2005 United States Grand Prix Tag 2005 Iditarod Radiation poisoning Bull Terrier Pulp Fiction Reservoir Dogs Socialization Chocolate Theory of conduct Battles of Lexington and Concor